<h2>ğŸ”‹ 5. Battery Rooms â€” A Lot of Energy in a Small Space</h2>

<p>This is where the stored power lives. And depending on the chemistry, the risk profile changes completely.</p>

<h3>Lead-Acid Rooms</h3>
<p>Reliable, but have their own quirks:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Hydrogen generation</li>
  <li>Ignition from sparks</li>
  <li>Thermal build-up</li>
  <li>High-current DC arcs</li>
  <li>Plastic cases that will burn nicely if theyâ€™re given the chance</li>
